-- Peru Stocks: Candente Copper, El Brocal, Panoro, Volcan
-- B y   A l e x   E m e r y
-- 2012-03-15T21:41:03Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-15/peru-stocks-candente-copper-el-brocal-panoro-volcan.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in  Peru  trading. Stock symbols are in parentheses
and share prices are as of 3:10 p.m. Lima time.  The  Lima General Index (IGBVL)  fell 0.2 percent to 22,974.79. The
 MSCI All Peru Capped Index (MXPECAPD)  slid 0.6 percent to 2,872.55.  Empresa Agroindustrial Pomalca SA (POM\C)  (POMALCC1 PE), a sugar
producer, fell 5.2 percent to 55 centimos. Peru’s sugarcane
harvests declined 1.7 percent through January from a year
earlier, the National Statistics Institute reported today.  Panoro Minerals Ltd. (PML)  , a Canadian copper and gold
exploration company, rose 2.6 percent to 79 cents after copper
rebounded in  New York , said  Daniel Romero , an analyst at Lima-
based investment fund NC&F Inversiones SA.  Candente Copper Corp. (DNT)  , a Canadian copper
exploration company, gained 1.9 percent to $1.06.  Volcan Cia. Minera SAA (VOLCAAC1)  (VOLCAAC1 PE), Peru’s largest zinc
and silver producer, climbed 1.8 percent to 5.20 soles after
zinc futures advanced in  London .  Sociedad Minera El Brocal SAA (SMBC)  (BROCALC1 PE), a zinc and
copper producer, rose 1 percent to 50 soles.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Alex Emery in Lima at 
